message.content: Most men in East Timor generally hold negative views towards abortion. They tend to believe that it is morally wrong and against their cultural and religious beliefs. They see it as a violation of the sanctity of life and often perceive it as an act of killing. Consequently, they tend to prioritize the preservation of life and the protection of unborn children. These views are influenced by traditional values, deep-rooted religious beliefs, and social norms prevalent in East Timor.
